sting & Validation\n529: \n530: - [ ] **T14.1** Test main.yml workflow locally with act\n531:   - Command: `act pull_request -j build` (if act available)\n532:   - Verify: Workflow syntax valid\n533: \n534: - [ ] **T14.2** Validate all workflow YAML syntax\n535:   - Run: `yamllint .github/workflows/*.yml` or similar\n536:   - Verify: All workflows pass YAML linting\n537: \n538: - [ ] **T14.3** Test path filters with sample PR\n539:   - Create test PR with Go file changes\n540:   - Verify: lint.yml triggers correctly\n541: \n542: - [ ] **T14.4** Test path filters with Python changes\n543:   - Create test PR with sdk-python changes\n544:   - Verify: python-sdk-tests.yml and python-lint.yml trigger\n545: \n546: - [ ] **T14.5** Test codespell workflow\n547:   - Introduce intentional typo in source file\n548:   - Verify: codespell.yml fails on PR\n549: \n550: - [ ] **T14.6** Test build-push-release.yml with test tag\n551:   - Push test tag `v9.9.9-test`\n552:   - Verify: Images built and pushed to GHCR\n553: \n554: - [ ] **T14.7** Verify Codecov integration\n555:   - Run test-coverage.yml on PR\n556:   - Verify: Coverage report uploads (if token configured)\n557: \n558: - [ ] **T14.8** Test e2e.yml workflow\n559:   - Create PR to main\n560:   - Verify: E2E tests run in Kind cluster\n561:   - Verify: Logs uploaded on failure\n562: \n563: ---\n564: \n565: ## Acceptance Criteria\n566: \n567: 1. ✅ All 12 workflow files created in `.github/workflows/`\n568: 2. ✅ `main.yml` builds Workload Manager Docker image on PR\n569: 3. ✅ `e2e.yml` runs E2E tests with Kind v0.30.0, captures logs\n570: 4. ✅ `lint.yml` runs golangci-lint only when Go code changes\n571: 5. ✅ `python-sdk-tests.yml` runs pytest on SDK changes\n572: 6. ✅ `python-lint.yml` runs Ruff from repo root on Python changes\n573: 7. ✅ `test-coverage.yml` runs coverage tests, uploads to Codecov\n574: 8. ✅ `codegen-check.yml` verifies generated code is up to date\n575: 9. ✅ `copyright-check.yml` ensures copyright headers are consistent\n576: 10. ✅ `codespell.yml` checks spelling with proper skip/ignore lists\n577: 11. ✅ `build-push-release.yml` publishes multi-arch images on tags\n578: 12. ✅ `dify-plugin-publish.yml` packages and submits Dify plugin\n579: 13. ✅ `workflows-approve.yml` auto-approves workflows for repeat contributors\n580: 14. ✅ All workflows use correct path filters via dorny/paths-filter\n581: 15. ✅ All workflows have proper conditional execution based on path changes\n582: 16. ✅ Release workflow uses correct action versions (v3/v4/v2 for compatibility)\n583: 17. ✅ E2E workflow captures and uploads failure artifacts\n584: 18. ✅ Coverage workflow supports workflow_call with optional token\n585: 19. ✅ All workflow names match specification\n586: 20. ✅ All triggers target correct branches (main, release-*)\n587: \n588: ---\n589: \n590: **Notes:**\n591: - Stage ST-3: Implementation complete (all 12 GitHub Actions workflows created)\n592: - Workflows cover: CI build, E2E, lint (Go/Python), SDK tests, coverage, codegen, copyright, codespell, release publishing, Dify plugin, workflow approval\n593: - Path filtering via `dorny/paths-filter@v3` for efficient conditional execution\n594: - E2E uses Kind with `install_only: true` to avoid double cluster creation\n595: - Release workflow publishes multi-arch images to GHCR\n596: - First-time contributor workflow approval prevents abuse while enabling CI\n597: \n598: (End of file)\n\n(End of file - total 598 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows) Tasks\n\n**Module:** .github  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Repository Structure & Shared Configuration\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create `.github/workflows/` directory structure\n  - Directory: `.github/workflows/`\n  - Verify: Directory exists for workflow files\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Define reusable path filter configurations\n  - Create path filter definitions for: `lint`, `coverage`, `python`, `codegen`, `copyright`\n  - Use `dorny/paths-filter` action patterns\n  - Verify: All path filters documented in workflow comments\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/ci-cd/AR-034-github-actions/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775884116288,"end":1775884116319}}}}
